E-commerce Website
Stylo is a complete, fully responsive e-commerce website template built using only HTML, CSS, and vanilla JavaScript. It provides a clean, modern, and attractive user interface for showcasing fashion products. The project is designed to be lightweight, easy to understand, and simple to customize.

Features
Fully Responsive Design: Looks great on all devices, from large desktops to small mobile phones.

Interactive UI Elements: Includes a pop-up newsletter subscription, a notification toast, and interactive product cards.

Dynamic Mobile Navigation: Features a slide-out sidebar and a bottom navigation bar for a seamless mobile experience.

Product Showcase: A well-organized grid to display new arrivals, trending items, and special deals.

Pure HTML, CSS & JS: Built with fundamental web technologies without any frameworks, making it easy for anyone to modify.

Attractive Styling: Enhanced with custom fonts from Google Fonts, smooth animations, and a modern color palette.

Technologies Used
HTML5: For the structure and content of the website.

CSS3: For all styling, layout, responsiveness, and animations.

Vanilla JavaScript: For all interactive features like the modal, mobile menu, and event handling.

How to Use
This project requires no complex setup or installation.

Create the Files: In a new folder, create three files:

index.html

style.css

script.js

Copy the Code: Copy the code from the project into the corresponding files.

Launch: Open the index.html file in your favorite web browser.

That's it! The website is now live on your local machine.

Customization
This template is designed to be easily customized.

Branding: To change the brand name, simply search for "Stylo" in the index.html file and replace it with your own.

Products & Images: The products are hardcoded directly into the index.html file. You can easily replace the placeholder image URLs, titles, and prices with your own product information.

Colors & Fonts: Most of the core colors and fonts can be changed by editing the CSS variables at the top of the style.css file.

